(power_pad, time).explanation: Power consumption of I/O pads does not directly influence processor execution time as pad power is primarily related to interface functionality rather than computational performance;

(power_pad, area_net_area).explanation: Larger net areas in processor designs require more extensive I/O infrastructure and pad connections, which directly increases the power consumption associated with I/O pads;

(power_pad, area_cell_area).explanation: Increased cell area in processor designs necessitates more I/O pads for signal routing and power distribution, directly leading to higher pad power consumption;
